    "comment": "Rationale: The paper describes the subcellular localization of delta-type opioid receptors in the axon terminals of the cervical spinal cord.\n\nFigure 3 and 5a shows that in axon terminals, immunoreactivity is localized to the membranes and lumen of dense-core vesicles (Fig. 3) at the peripheral\nportion of the axon terminal, away from the synaptic specialization.\nFigure 3A shows labelling at segments of the axonal plasma membrane.\nFigure 3B and 5a show an axon terminal with immunoreactivity located along the dcv and a segment of the plasma membrane.\nThe paper reports that in axon terminals, immunoperoxidase could also be localized to membranes of numerous small clear vesicles.\n\n2/7/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: 'For light and electron microscopy, adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (200&300 gm)\nwere deeply anesthetized with sodium pentobarbital (50 mg/kg i.p.) and perfused through the ascending aorta with 50 ml of 3.75% acrolein...'",
